\section{Implementation Stack}\label{sec:sys:stack}

The codebase is Python~3.11, managed with \texttt{uv}. Orchestration uses
LangGraph~\cite{langgraph2024}; observability uses Langfuse~\cite{langfuse2024};
the statistical pipeline uses \texttt{pandas}~\cite{pandas2020},
\texttt{numpy}~\cite{harris2020array}, and \texttt{scipy}~\cite{virtanen2020scipy}.
Provider SDKs are wrapped in a unified \texttt{ModelClient} that records, per call,
prompt tokens, completion tokens, cache-read tokens (where supported), wall-clock
latency, and provider-billed cost. The wrapper supports 19 model identifiers; only the 11 listed in
Table~\ref{tab:models} are exercised in official runs. The remaining 8 identifiers
cover open-weights models excluded per Section~\ref{sec:meth:models} and two
non-CUAD test configurations not evaluated in this study.

