\paragraph{M6 --- Consolidated specialist (architectural ablation).}\label{sec:sys:m6}\label{sec:sys:m1-vs-m6}
Its prompt is the textual union of the three M1 specialist prompts, concatenated
into a single agent with no router, no orchestrator, and no per-category branching:
%
\begin{equation*}
  \texttt{prompt}_{\text{M6}} = \mathrm{join}\!\left(
    \texttt{prompt}_{\text{risk}},\;
    \texttt{prompt}_{\text{temporal}},\;
    \texttt{prompt}_{\text{ip}}
  \right)
\end{equation*}
%
The three preambles are separated by domain headings; the verbatim-span output
contract is stated once at the end. M6's purpose is methodological: M1 vs.\ M6
isolates routing and decomposition; M6 vs.\ B0 isolates prompt content. Together
the two contrasts decompose the M1-vs-B0 delta into an architectural component and a
prompt-content component, which is the basis for the routing-redundancy finding in
Section~\ref{sec:res:h3}.

\section{Observability and Trace Schema}\label{sec:sys:trace}\label{sec:auditability}

\paragraph{What is recorded.}
For each clause-level decision the system captures:
(i)~configuration ID and model identifier;
(ii)~prompt template ID, version, and rendered prompt;
(iii)~full model completion;
(iv)~parsed final answer with parser version and status;
(v)~routing decision (M1) or classifier verdict (M0) where applicable;
(vi)~per-call token counts, billed cost, and wall-clock latency.
M1 traces are parent--child structured: the router call is the parent, the specialist
call is its child. Listing~\ref{lst:trace} shows a representative M1 record.

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={Representative M1 trace record (abridged JSONL).},
  label={lst:trace}, basicstyle=\scriptsize\ttfamily, frame=single]
{
  "contract_id": "CUAD_0231",
  "category":    "Cap On Liability",
  "config_id":   "M1",
  "model_id":    "claude-sonnet-4-6-20251001",
  "calls": [
    { "role":       "router",
      "prompt_id":  "m1_router/v3",
      "completion": "{\"specialist\":\"risk_liability\",\"reasoning\":\"...\"}",
      "tokens_in":  412,   "tokens_out": 18,
      "latency_ms": 380,   "cost_usd": 0.0008,
      "parent_id":  null },
    { "role":       "specialist_risk_liability",
